<% const pageTitle = 'data export' %>
<%- include('partials/header', { pageTitle }) %>

<article class="prose">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Data export (GDPR right of access)</h1>
    <p class="muted">Download a complete machine-readable copy of every piece of data PreXiv holds about your account.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="form-section">
    <h2>What's in the export</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Your account row</strong> — username, email, profile fields, karma, admin status, ORCID, timestamps. <em>Excludes</em> the bcrypt password hash and the TOTP secret.</li>
      <li><strong>Every manuscript you've submitted</strong> — full row including abstract, conductor metadata, auditor metadata, withdrawal status, scores, and the path to any uploaded PDF.</li>
      <li><strong>Every comment you've written</strong>, with score and timestamps.</li>
      <li><strong>Every vote you've cast</strong> — target type, target id, value, when.</li>
      <li><strong>Every flag you've filed</strong>, including resolution status and any moderator note.</li>
      <li><strong>Every API token you've minted</strong> — name, last-used / created timestamps. We do <em>not</em> include the plaintext token (we don't have it) or the hash.</li>
      <li><strong>Every webhook subscription you've registered</strong>, with delivery status. Secrets are <em>not</em> included.</li>
      <li><strong>Notifications</strong> addressed to you, if the in-app notifications subsystem is enabled.</li>
      <li><strong>Audit-log entries</strong> where you are the actor or the named target.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The export is JSON; we recommend piping it through <code>jq</code> for reading.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="form-section">
    <h2>Download</h2>
    <p>
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/me/export">Download my data (JSON)</a>
    </p>
    <p class="muted small">
      Or use the API: <code>curl -H 'Authorization: Bearer prexiv_…' <%= apiBase %>/me/export</code>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="form-section">
    <h2>Other rights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> edit your <a href="/u/<%= escapeHtml(user.username) %>">profile</a> or any of <a href="/u/<%= escapeHtml(user.username) %>">your submissions</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> <a href="/me/delete-account">delete your account</a>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted small">See <a href="/privacy">the privacy policy</a> for the full picture.</p>
  </section>
</article>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
